# ORIG TITLE    Dutch man arrested in Spain for cyber attack against anti-spam company . 
# ORIG CONTENT  A Dutch man has been arrested in Spain in connection with a cyber-attack against an international company that filters out spam emails called Spamhaus. The 35-year-old who has not been named was the subject of an international arrest warrant. He is believed to have driven around in Spain, using mobile technology in his van in an attack last month against non-profit company Spamhaus, who are based in London and Geneva. Spamhaus partner companies in the US, UK and the Netherlands were also targeted. 
